 - paper title: Entransy theory for the optimization of heat transfer – A review and update
 - abstract: Abstract   Heat transfer optimization methods to effectively improve heat transfer performance is of great importance for energy conservation and pollution reduction. A recently developed heat transfer optimization method based on entransy theory and related peer-reviewed papers published between 2003 and 2010 are reviewed and updated in this paper to describe entransy, entransy dissipation, optimization criteria and optimization principles and their applications to different heat transfer modes (thermal conduction, convection and radiation) and to different levels (heat transfer element, heat exchanger, and heat exchanger network). Entransy theory is then compared with entropy theory in several aspects, including the heat transfer purpose, irreversibility and optimization principle for energy savings or weight reductions of thermal facilities. Finally, entransy theory is also compared with constructal theory in terms of optimization objective, optimization method and optimized results.
 - publication date: 2013-08-01
 - venue: International Journal of Heat and Mass Transfer

Candidate: 1737648 
 - paper title: Comments on “Temperature–heat diagram analysis method for heat recovery physical adsorption refrigeration cycle – Taking multi-stage cycle as an example”
 - abstract: Abstract   The purpose of this discussion is to increase the awareness of the divergent views on the entransy concept among the readers of International Journal of Refrigeration. Comments are presented in particular on the paper by Xu et al. where the authors used entransy dissipation in their analysis. Based on the view points of various independent groups of researchers worldwide, I draw the attention of readers to the reality that entransy has no physical meaning.
 - publication date: 2017-10-01
 - venue: International Journal of Refrigeration-revue Internationale Du Froid

