ive region located in the area more than 50. from the solar centre and five without corresponding MDI data, the beta magnetic field configuration (about 47 per cent; 36 out of 77) is more likely to form eruptive filaments than the other ones and there are 33 filament eruptions associated with magnetic flux cancellation, 42 events associated with magnetic flux emergence and two events without variation of magnetic field. The average area of emergence regions is 855.9 arcsec(2). These findings may be instructive not only in respect to the modelling of active-region filament eruptions but also in predicting flares and CMEs.
 - publication date: 2011-07-11
 - venue: Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society

